const v12ReadA={id:"v12-read-a",kind:"passage",label:"Passage for Items 69-72",title:"Appointment Window Pilot",description:"A city records office tested appointment windows for requests that usually required document checking. Walk-in service remained available, but two counters were reserved for clients who selected a 20-minute window online or by telephone. During the first month, appointed clients waited less, while walk-in waits increased slightly between 10 a.m. and noon. The office then limited appointments during those hours and assigned a floating clerk whenever the walk-in queue exceeded twelve people. Both groups' waits improved in the second month. Before expanding the pilot, managers planned to compare missed appointments, staffing hours, and service completion rates rather than relying only on average waiting time.",alt:"Passage about a records office testing appointment windows, adjusting appointment volume and staffing after walk-in waits rose, and planning a broader evaluation using several measures."};
const v12ReadB={id:"v12-read-b",kind:"passage",label:"Babasahin para sa Aytem 73-76",title:"Palitan ng Binhi",description:"Nagbukas ang samahan ng mga magsasaka ng lingguhang palitan ng binhi upang mapanatili ang mga lokal na uri ng gulay. Sa unang buwan, kaunti ang nagdala ng binhi dahil hindi malinaw kung paano itatala ang pinagmulan at petsa ng pag-ani. Gumawa ang samahan ng payak na kard na may tatlong kailangang detalye at nagtalaga ng isang boluntaryong tutulong sa pagsulat. Dumami ang kalahok, ngunit napansin nilang may ilang pakete na kulang sa impormasyon tungkol sa paraan ng pag-iimbak. Sa susunod na pulong, susubukan nila ang kard na may larawan at maikling paalala tungkol sa pagpapatuyo at lalagyan.",alt:"Teksto tungkol sa palitan ng lokal na binhi, simpleng kard para sa pinagmulan at petsa ng pag-ani, tulong ng boluntaryo, at planong magdagdag ng gabay sa wastong pag-iimbak."};
const v12ReadC={id:"v12-read-c",kind:"passage",label:"Passage for Items 77-80",title:"Accessible Museum Labels",description:"A municipal museum replaced several dense exhibit labels with shorter text, larger type, and a QR code linking to audio descriptions. Visitors completed the gallery more quickly, but staff could not tell whether they understood more or simply read less. The museum then added three optional questions at the exit and invited a disability group to review the audio controls. The group found that the QR pages worked with screen readers but that the play button lacked a clear label. After the button was corrected, the museum scheduled a comparison of comprehension, device use, and visitor satisfaction across the old and revised galleries.",alt:"Passage about a museum revising exhibit labels and audio descriptions, discovering an unlabeled play button through accessibility review, and planning a multi-measure comparison."};
